2629
02:19:17.755 --> 02:19:18.905
Thank you for the opportunity

2630
02:19:19.005 --> 02:19:21.785
to provide a submission on the Healthy Futures

2631
02:19:21.795 --> 02:19:22.825
Prior Order Amendment.

2632
02:19:22.855 --> 02:19:25.545
Bill. We're here to speak to the submission

2633
02:19:25.605 --> 02:19:26.825
of the Medical Council

2634
02:19:27.065 --> 02:19:29.765
of New Zealand Council is the regulator

2635
02:19:30.025 --> 02:19:31.405
for the medical profession.

2636
02:19:32.245 --> 02:19:34.845
I understand our written submission should be taken as read.

2637
02:19:35.305 --> 02:19:37.165
So this oral submission is intended

2638
02:19:37.185 --> 02:19:39.885
to ensure the select committee is clear about

2639
02:19:40.225 --> 02:19:42.885
how the Medical Council's submission is connected

2640
02:19:42.885 --> 02:19:44.685
with its role to protect public safety

2641
02:19:45.685 --> 02:19:48.805
and how one aspect of the bill could impact this.

2642
02:19:50.025 --> 02:19:53.765
Our submission relates solely to clause 16 of the bill.

2643
02:19:53.985 --> 02:19:56.885
As you know, that clause removes the requirement

2644
02:19:56.945 --> 02:19:59.565
to ensure Health New Zealand maintains systems

2645
02:19:59.665 --> 02:20:02.485
and processes to ensure it has the capacity

2646
02:20:02.505 --> 02:20:05.845
and capability to understand the Treaty of wgi

2647
02:20:06.605 --> 02:20:08.085
culturally appropriate health services

2648
02:20:08.145 --> 02:20:10.365
for Maori grounded in Maori knowledge

2649
02:20:10.365 --> 02:20:14.035
and customs that are whanau centered Maori perspectives

2650
02:20:14.035 --> 02:20:17.595
of services and more broadly cultural safety

2651
02:20:17.815 --> 02:20:21.315
and responsiveness of services for patients of any culture

2652
02:20:21.535 --> 02:20:22.555
or ethnicity.

2653
02:20:23.675 --> 02:20:27.735
The reason we have an interest in clause 16 of the bill is

2654
02:20:27.735 --> 02:20:29.975
because the medical Council's primary purpose is

2655
02:20:29.975 --> 02:20:30.975
to protect the public.

2656
02:20:31.795 --> 02:20:36.015
Two important ways it does that are to set standards for

2657
02:20:36.015 --> 02:20:39.615
how doctors are trained and the way they practice medicine.

2658
02:20:40.465 --> 02:20:43.135
These standards require doctors to develop skills

2659
02:20:43.235 --> 02:20:45.175
and understanding of cultural competence

2660
02:20:45.275 --> 02:20:48.815
and cultural safety in, in the New Zealand context,

2661
02:20:49.185 --> 02:20:51.775
given our history, population makeup

2662
02:20:52.315 --> 02:20:54.215
and inequities and health outcomes.

2663
02:20:54.835 --> 02:20:57.535
At a practical level, it makes sense for doctors

2664
02:20:57.955 --> 02:20:59.935
to be trained to have the skills

2665
02:21:00.115 --> 02:21:03.335
and understanding to provide health services in a way

2666
02:21:03.335 --> 02:21:05.575
that is culturally safe for Maori.

2667
02:21:06.155 --> 02:21:07.615
But this is not exclusive.

2668
02:21:07.675 --> 02:21:09.855
The medical council set standards

2669
02:21:09.915 --> 02:21:12.255
to ensure doctors are culturally competent

2670
02:21:12.395 --> 02:21:15.735
and safe to treat patients of all cultures and ethnicities.

2671
02:21:16.845 --> 02:21:18.865
The section of the act, which Clause 16

2672
02:21:18.965 --> 02:21:21.425
of the bill is amending, aligns with

2673
02:21:21.485 --> 02:21:24.825
and supports what the medical Council does in this area.

2674
02:21:25.775 --> 02:21:28.045
Since Health New Zealand employs around half

2675
02:21:28.105 --> 02:21:31.245
of the doctors in New Zealand, removing this requirement,

2676
02:21:31.355 --> 02:21:34.765
undercuts council's efforts to promote a consistent standard

2677
02:21:34.825 --> 02:21:36.965
of health care throughout New Zealand.

2678
02:21:37.955 --> 02:21:40.695
And just to be clear about the statutory requirement,

2679
02:21:40.695 --> 02:21:42.295
which Clause 16 is removing,

2680
02:21:42.925 --> 02:21:46.095
it's about health New Zealand having systems, processes,

2681
02:21:46.335 --> 02:21:49.695
capabilities, and capacity for cultural safety.

2682
02:21:49.765 --> 02:21:51.735
When providing health services to Maori

2683
02:21:51.735 --> 02:21:52.815
and all other patients.

2684
02:21:53.565 --> 02:21:56.095
It's not about providing different health services

2685
02:21:56.475 --> 02:21:58.975
or different treatment based on ethnicity

2686
02:21:59.715 --> 02:22:00.925
Against this background

2687
02:22:00.985 --> 02:22:02.445
and underlying our concern

2688
02:22:02.795 --> 02:22:05.325
with the proposed amendment is Council's view

2689
02:22:05.325 --> 02:22:08.565
that cultural safety is integral to effective clinical care.

2690
02:22:09.725 --> 02:22:11.965
Cultural safety is focused on creating an environment

2691
02:22:11.965 --> 02:22:14.805
where people from diverse cultural backgrounds feel

2692
02:22:14.805 --> 02:22:17.445
respected, safe and empowered.

2693
02:22:17.975 --> 02:22:21.525
There is a growing body of evidence that culturally safe

2694
02:22:22.605 --> 02:22:25.685
practices lead to improved health outcomes, particularly

2695
02:22:25.865 --> 02:22:28.445
for marginalized or underserved communities.

2696
02:22:29.595 --> 02:22:32.355
Cultural biases and assumptions can impact a

2697
02:22:32.355 --> 02:22:33.435
doctor's consultation.

2698
02:22:34.225 --> 02:22:37.515
They may influence how thorough a doctor is in their

2699
02:22:37.515 --> 02:22:40.635
assessment of the patient, the tests or treatment offered,

2700
02:22:41.175 --> 02:22:42.875
or whether a patient feels comfortable

2701
02:22:43.515 --> 02:22:45.835
approaching their doctor to access health services.

2702
02:22:46.775 --> 02:22:48.155
To look at a New Zealand example,

2703
02:22:48.445 --> 02:22:51.515
Maori women have been significantly less likely than

2704
02:22:51.515 --> 02:22:52.715
New Zealand, European women

2705
02:22:52.935 --> 02:22:54.715
to access breast screening services.

2706
02:22:55.595 --> 02:22:58.435
A 2015 study of breast cancer patients showed

2707
02:22:58.435 --> 02:23:02.355
that Maori women who were not screened had a 60% higher

2708
02:23:02.355 --> 02:23:05.915
likelihood of dying from breast cancer than non-Maori women.

2709
02:23:06.775 --> 02:23:10.475
But the study also found there was no significant difference

2710
02:23:10.615 --> 02:23:12.435
in survival rates between Maori

2711
02:23:12.435 --> 02:23:14.395
and non-Maori women where they had

2712
02:23:14.655 --> 02:23:15.955
access screening services.

2713
02:23:16.765 --> 02:23:19.595
These differences highlight while providing a culturally

2714
02:23:19.625 --> 02:23:22.155
safe environment for accessing health services.

2715
02:23:22.615 --> 02:23:25.515
In this case, breast screening can overcome significant

2716
02:23:25.515 --> 02:23:28.675
health inequities while making the same services available

2717
02:23:29.055 --> 02:23:31.195
to all cultural and ethnic groups.

2718
02:23:31.865 --> 02:23:34.075
Therefore, it's important that our largest employer

2719
02:23:34.095 --> 02:23:37.155
of doctors and health professionals should support its

2720
02:23:37.355 --> 02:23:38.915
employees to understand how

2721
02:23:38.915 --> 02:23:42.195
to provide care in a culturally safe manner that

2722
02:23:42.385 --> 02:23:44.835
that enables equal access to health services.

2723
02:23:45.895 --> 02:23:47.275
The council's further concerns

2724
02:23:47.275 --> 02:23:49.435
with the amendment are set out in our written submission.

2725
02:23:49.435 --> 02:23:51.795
But briefly, these include that first,

2726
02:23:52.305 --> 02:23:55.635
despite the council's setting, continuing to set standards

2727
02:23:55.635 --> 02:23:57.395
for cultural safety and competence.

2728
02:23:57.815 --> 02:23:59.675
And future doctors are less likely

2729
02:23:59.735 --> 02:24:02.435
to be working alongside other staff at Health New Zealand

2730
02:24:02.775 --> 02:24:04.075
who are culturally competent.

2731
02:24:04.535 --> 02:24:07.475
So the work environment overall will be less conducive

2732
02:24:07.535 --> 02:24:09.315
for patients of all ethnicities

2733
02:24:09.855 --> 02:24:11.435
to access culturally sound care,

2734
02:24:11.805 --> 02:24:14.795
which would negatively impact health outcomes over time.

2735
02:24:15.775 --> 02:24:17.475
Second, it will limit health.

2736
02:24:17.495 --> 02:24:20.475
New Zealand's ability to support overseas trained doctors

2737
02:24:20.975 --> 02:24:22.155
to settle into work

2738
02:24:22.535 --> 02:24:24.155
and deliver healthcare in a way

2739
02:24:24.155 --> 02:24:26.915
that is effective in the New Zealand environment.

2740
02:24:27.445 --> 02:24:31.675
These doctors are a key part of our workforce, yet 40% leave

2741
02:24:31.675 --> 02:24:35.755
after one year and 60% after two years in New Zealand.

2742
02:24:36.715 --> 02:24:38.355
Removing the requirement for Health New Zealand

2743
02:24:38.775 --> 02:24:39.955
to maintain capability

2744
02:24:40.015 --> 02:24:43.915
and cultural safety would be a backward step in retaining

2745
02:24:44.155 --> 02:24:46.635
overseas trained doctors in our medical workforce.

2746
02:24:47.925 --> 02:24:50.395
Third, it will diminish health New Zealand's incentive

2747
02:24:50.395 --> 02:24:52.715
to provide doctors with further education

2748
02:24:52.775 --> 02:24:56.235
and resources to ensure workplace systems support them

2749
02:24:56.535 --> 02:24:58.155
to deliver culturally safe care.

2750
02:24:58.895 --> 02:25:01.955
Fourth, it may increase the risk of avoidable harm

2751
02:25:01.975 --> 02:25:03.475
to patients and their families

2752
02:25:03.895 --> 02:25:05.555
by reinforcing a clinical culture

2753
02:25:05.985 --> 02:25:08.515
that doesn't support a patient's unique requirements

2754
02:25:08.695 --> 02:25:09.955
and patient-centered care.

2755
02:25:10.885 --> 02:25:13.225
And finally, there is a trans Tasman dimension.

2756
02:25:13.655 --> 02:25:16.825
Australia has made great strides in embedding cultural

2757
02:25:16.825 --> 02:25:19.585
safety in medical education and practice.

2758
02:25:20.205 --> 02:25:22.385
We share key medical training structures

2759
02:25:22.765 --> 02:25:25.765
and processes with the Australian health regulators,

2760
02:25:26.055 --> 02:25:29.725
which support patient-centered care New Zealand would drop

2761
02:25:29.725 --> 02:25:32.285
behind and fall out of alignment with Australia.

2762
02:25:32.865 --> 02:25:36.365
If we backtrack on cultural safety in our health system

2763
02:25:37.065 --> 02:25:39.605
for all of these reasons, the medical council would

2764
02:25:39.605 --> 02:25:41.965
encourage the select committee to consider

2765
02:25:41.985 --> 02:25:45.365
how enacting Clause 16 will negatively impact not just

2766
02:25:45.575 --> 02:25:48.845
Maori, but all underserved populations such

2767
02:25:48.845 --> 02:25:50.925
as immigrant communities, Pacifica,

2768
02:25:51.305 --> 02:25:53.045
or those patients with disabilities.

2769
02:25:53.885 --> 02:25:57.085
Removing legislative emphasis on cultural safety risks,

2770
02:25:57.125 --> 02:25:59.645
perpetuating health inequities, as well

2771
02:25:59.645 --> 02:26:02.005
as reducing the opportunity for tailored

2772
02:26:02.385 --> 02:26:05.285
and appropriate patient care for all New Zealanders.

2773
02:26:05.655 --> 02:26:06.655
Thank you.

2774
02:26:07.415 --> 02:26:07.885
Thank you.

2775
02:26:12.905 --> 02:26:14.345
I don't agree with this bill,

2776
02:26:14.485 --> 02:26:18.425
but I suppose one might have a view that, uh,

2777
02:26:19.015 --> 02:26:23.225
good care can be delivered that is not culturally sensitive.

2778
02:26:23.795 --> 02:26:28.225
Could you please, uh, explain whether, uh,

2779
02:26:28.485 --> 02:26:30.625
how cultural sensitivity is

2780
02:26:30.645 --> 02:26:33.105
or is not part of good medical practice?

2781
02:26:38.195 --> 02:26:42.515
Cultural safety is about providing care that is, um,

2782
02:26:43.475 --> 02:26:46.635
specific to that person's needs no matter who the person is.

2783
02:26:47.095 --> 02:26:49.515
So if you're providing culturally safe care,

2784
02:26:50.305 --> 02:26:52.835
then it's respecting that person what they need,

2785
02:26:53.015 --> 02:26:55.035
and the outcomes going to be better for that person.

2786
02:26:55.695 --> 02:26:59.355
But often cultural safety is connected with care for Maori,

2787
02:26:59.535 --> 02:27:02.155
but what we've, what the research has demonstrated is what's

2788
02:27:02.155 --> 02:27:03.595
good for Maori is good for all patients.

2789
02:27:03.775 --> 02:27:04.775
So done.

2790
02:27:05.405 --> 02:27:06.865
Thank you. Oh no,

2791
02:27:06.865 --> 02:27:08.505
that was great. That was awesome. Alright.

2792
02:27:09.475 --> 02:27:11.265
Thank you very much for your submission today.

2793
